oto/132288268.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/after-a-sheriff-died-investigators-opened-his-locked-desk-drawer-and-reportedly-found-evidence-tied-to-stolen-drug-seizure-cash-raising-new-questions-about-how-seized-money-was-handled/articleshow/132288268.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/after-a-sheriff-died-investigators-opened-his-locked-desk-drawer-and-reportedly-found-evidence-tied-to-stolen-drug-seizure-cash-raising-new-questions-about-how-seized-money-was-handled/articleshow/132288268.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T19:16:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132288358,imgsize-1062871.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists find nanoplastics in Antarctic soil for the first time, including tyre-wear particles, raising concerns that tiny plastic pollution can travel through the atmosphere to Earth's most remote places]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132288816.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a groundbreaking study, scientists have identified nanoplastics in the pristine soils of Antarctica for the very first time. These microscopic plastic particles journey through the atmosphere, reaching even the most isolated regions. Analysis of soil samples revealed contamination from tyre wear and everyday plastic products. It suggests that both local human activities and far-reaching atmospheric movements contribute to this alarming trend, underscoring the widespread impact of plastic pollution worldwide.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-find-nanoplastics-in-antarctic-soil-for-the-first-time-including-tyre-wear-particles-raising-concerns-that-tiny-plastic-pollution-can-travel-through-the-atmosphere-to-earths-most-remote-places/articleshow/132288816.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-find-nanoplastics-in-antarctic-soil-for-the-first-time-including-tyre-wear-particles-raising-concerns-that-tiny-plastic-pollution-can-travel-through-the-atmosphere-to-earths-most-remote-places/articleshow/132288816.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T20:20:02+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132289723,imgsize-431162.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Researchers discover cave with rare cave pearls in Vietnam's Phong Nha-Ke Bang National Park]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132288507.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/researchers-discover-cave-with-rare-cave-pearls-in-vietnams-phong-nha-ke-bang-national-park/articleshow/132288507.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/researchers-discover-cave-with-rare-cave-pearls-in-vietnams-phong-nha-ke-bang-national-park/articleshow/132288507.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T19:29:11+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132288558,imgsize-1384563.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mosque effigy atop Northern Ireland bonfire sparks outrage; man arrested after anti-Muslim display]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132289802.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/mosque-effigy-atop-northern-ireland-bonfire-sparks-outrage-man-arrested-after-anti-muslim-display/articleshow/132289802.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/mosque-effigy-atop-northern-ireland-bonfire-sparks-outrage-man-arrested-after-anti-muslim-display/articleshow/132289802.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T20:37:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132289979,imgsize-91846.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists have filmed a rare 125-million-year-old goblin shark alive in its natural deep-sea habitat for the first time, revealing a new depth record and a wider Pacific range]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132288238.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[For the very first time, scientists have captured live footage of goblin sharks in their deep-sea environment, revealing new insights into the species. This remarkable finding extends their known depth by almost 700 meters. Observations from two separate instances identified these elusive sharks in previously unknown Pacific Ocean habitats, complemented by archived footage from 2019 that documented an unrecognized encounter. This groundbreaking research broadens the goblin shark's recognized range significantly.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-have-filmed-a-rare-125-million-year-old-goblin-shark-alive-in-its-natural-deep-sea-habitat-for-the-first-time-revealing-a-new-depth-record-and-a-wider-pacific-range/articleshow/132288238.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-have-filmed-a-rare-125-million-year-old-goblin-shark-alive-in-its-natural-deep-sea-habitat-for-the-first-time-revealing-a-new-depth-record-and-a-wider-pacific-range/articleshow/132288238.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T19:29:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132288498,imgsize-24974.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‎Meet Bakari, the 21-year-old gorilla chosen to lead Disney's famous troop after the death of its longtime silverback]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132281343.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Bakari, a 21-year-old male gorilla, has joined Animal Kingdom as the new troop leader. He arrived from the Saint Louis Zoo as part of a conservation program. Bakari takes over leadership after the passing of Gino, the former troop leader. Gino had led the gorilla troop for nearly three decades at the park. This transfer marks a new chapter for the park's western lowland gorillas.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-bakari-the-21-year-old-gorilla-chosen-to-lead-disneys-famous-troop-after-the-death-of-its-longtime-silverback/articleshow/132281343.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-bakari-the-21-year-old-gorilla-chosen-to-lead-disneys-famous-troop-after-the-death-of-its-longtime-silverback/articleshow/132281343.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T19:15:36+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132281636,imgsize-263089.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Lake Powell and Lake Mead are both running dangerously low, and scientists now say one radical idea could help: drain most of Lake Powell and store the water in Lake Mead instead]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132284490.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A Colorado River expert suggests moving water from Lake Powell to Lake Mead. This proposal addresses ongoing drought conditions impacting western United States water supplies. Lake Powell's dam infrastructure limits usable water storage, while Lake Mead offers greater capacity. The plan involves gradual water transfer and potential exposure of Glen Canyon. This strategy aims for long-term water management solutions for millions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/lake-powell-and-lake-mead-are-both-running-dangerously-low-and-scientists-now-say-one-radical-idea-could-help-drain-most-of-lake-powell-and-store-the-water-in-lake-mead-instead/articleshow/132284490.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/lake-powell-and-lake-mead-are-both-running-dangerously-low-and-scientists-now-say-one-radical-idea-could-help-drain-most-of-lake-powell-and-store-the-water-in-lake-mead-instead/articleshow/132284490.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T19:19:09+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132285365,imgsize-143835.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Orlando Bloom bought this Beverly Hills home for $7 million, redesigned it for 18 months, sold it for about the same price, and now it rents for $31,000 a month]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132281912.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Orlando Bloom's former Beverly Hills residence is now available as a luxury rental. This property, which Bloom renovated extensively, is listed for thirty-one thousand dollars monthly. The four-bedroom house is situated in the prestigious Trousdale Estates neighborhood. It offers stunning city and ocean views, and remains fully furnished for its new occupants. Bloom previously sold this home after breaking even on his initial purchase price.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/orlando-bloom-bought-this-beverly-hills-home-for-7-million-redesigned-it-for-18-months-sold-it-for-about-the-same-price-and-now-it-rents-for-31000-a-month/articleshow/132281912.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/orlando-bloom-bought-this-beverly-hills-home-for-7-million-redesigned-it-for-18-months-sold-it-for-about-the-same-price-and-now-it-rents-for-31000-a-month/articleshow/132281912.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T19:22:05+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Real Estate Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132282577,imgsize-124046.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A 2,500-year-old warrior prince tomb found in Italy had a chariot, helmet and weapons still inside]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132288519.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Archaeologists in Italy have unearthed a 2,500-year-old tomb of a pre-Roman warrior prince. This royal burial was found in Sirolo and belonged to the ancient Piceni civilization. The warrior prince was buried with a two-wheeled chariot and weapons. Nearby, a woman's burial contained textiles and ancient metal pins. This discovery sheds new light on the Piceni elite and their burial practices.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-2500-year-old-warrior-prince-tomb-found-in-italy-had-a-chariot-helmet-and-weapons-still-inside/articleshow/132288519.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-2500-year-old-warrior-prince-tomb-found-in-italy-had-a-chariot-helmet-and-weapons-still-inside/articleshow/132288519.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T19:25:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</